Jacques Chirac &apos;s lasting political legacy
Former French President Jacques Chirac died on Sunday at the age of 86 .
In a change the world hasn ’ t seen in a century , much of the French politician ’ s political legacy still deserves our praise .
Chirac served in a charismatic manner as President of France for 12 years .
Inheritor of the independent diplomatic spirit of Gaullism , and a staunch supporter of European integration , he was a leading figure in the pursuit of the “ European dream . ”
He is also a strong advocate of world multipolarity and multilateralism , and is a strategic politician .
As a result , the French media described him as &quot; an outstanding representative of France on the world stage &quot; .
One of Mr Chirac &apos;s most celebrated political decisions was to oppose the US-led war in Iraq .
Together with Germany , France was at the forefront of the war against pressure from the United States .
A year after the war broke out , he predicted that the war in Iraq would lead to an increase in terrorist activity and make the world more dangerous .
Chirac &apos;s warning proved to be correct .
At a time of the collapse of European integration and the increasing salience of American unilateralism , Chirac has a strong sense of enlightenment for the strategic thinking and choice of international politics and global affairs .
Chirac was also a French politician who was familiar and kind to the Chinese .
He was one of the advocates and creators of the “ golden decade ” of Sino-French relations , which accelerated with the strategic vision of a statesman when he was first elected to the French presidency in 1995 .
In 2004 , China and France established a comprehensive strategic partnership and their bilateral exchanges entered an entirely new stage .
Under Chirac , bilateral trade between China and France has grown rapidly , and the two countries have made breakthroughs in their bilateral cooperation in such fields as aviation , nuclear energy and railway transportation .
The Year of Sino-French Culture initiated by Jacques Chirac has created a completely new model of cultural exchanges in the history of China and France .
Chirac &apos;s lifelong love for Chinese culture has been particularly impressive .
Chirac can recite some of the poems of Li Bai and Du Fu , and even accurately determine the age of the Chinese bronzes , according to Chinese diplomats who know him well .
&quot; Do not look at the pyramid has not really been to Egypt , do not look at the Terra Cotta Warriors has not really been to China &quot; - this golden sentence from Chirac .
&quot; The West is concerned about China &apos;s political and social development , the ecological problems arising from China &apos;s economic growth , and China &apos;s position in international politics , &quot; Chirac once said in an interview with Xinhua .
But I personally have a lot of confidence in China .
I believe that China is a country with a long history of civilization and that its experience is sufficient to help it to establish its ideas and values for achieving harmonious development and to assume its long-term responsibilities on the world stage .
I also believe that China &apos;s renaissance will bring new creative vitality to world culture and enrich the world .
The Spin is gone , but Chirac &apos;s political legacy and message to the world will live on .
