Paris , March 26 ( Xinhua ) -- Both houses of the French parliament will discuss immigration policy reform next week , the European Times reported on Thursday .
French President Emmanuel Macron recently stated that France could not “ accommodate everyone . ”
According to the report , Macron is trying to find a compromise on immigration in order to ease the impact of the upcoming debate .
In a recent interview during the UN General Assembly ’ s general debate in New York , Macron expressed hope for a truly “ two-pronged ” approach to migration policy that strikes a balance between humanitarianism and efficiency .
&quot; If France wants to be able to accommodate ( migrants ) properly , it cannot accommodate everyone , &quot; Macron said .
Macron outlined four pillars of migration policy : the granting of asylum as quickly as possible to refugees in need of protection ; more efficient integration of migrants ; the reception and protection of all migrants who enter French territory ; and more efficient resettlement of those who are in France illegally and unfit to stay .
Whether illegal immigrants should be protected by the State Medical Assistance ( AME ) system has been the subject of much debate .
Mr Macron said he wanted to “ assess ” the system , not to eliminate it , but to limit it .
Following Macron ’ s remarks , the leader of the far-right “ National Alliance , ” Marine Le Pen , tweeted that Macron ’ s announcement was “ empty talk . ”
A member of the right-wing Republican faction , Senate President Rascher , also said that immigration policy should be discussed in a way that is &quot; moderate &quot; but &quot; realistic &quot; , an indirect criticism of Macron .
Varao , a member of the leftist Socialist Party , argued that France should “ accept more and better ” when it comes to immigration , and criticized Macron ’ s &quot; manipulation &quot; of the issue .
The report points out that the new Asylum and Immigration Act , which has been in force for a year , has divided opinion within the ruling party while failing to placate the right-wing opposition party .
Macron ’ s need to do something on the subject of immigration policy will once again be a point of attack for the far right at the next general election in 2022 , but will also risk infuriating the ruling party on the left .
It has been reported that immigration policy will be debated in the lower house of the French National Assembly from September 30 and in the Senate from October 2 .
China ’ s A-shares are showing signs of a “ buy-back wave ” , with many listed companies coming up with “ real gold and silver ” to buy back shares .
According to the financial data service Oriental Wealth , as of July 27 , the total buybacks implemented in 2019 by A-listed companies had exceeded 100 billion yuan ( RMB , the same below ) , far more than in the same period of the previous year .
In response , Xu Yang , chairman of Shanghai Maikorong Information Consulting Co . , Ltd . , said that the overall valuation of the A-share market is low this year , and buying back shares at a relatively low price helps listed companies make more efficient use of capital . It also reflects listed companies &apos; willingness to actively manage market value and abundant cash flow , helping to boost investors &apos; confidence .
In addition , the continuously perfect share repurchase system , has also promoted the listed company active share repurchase .
At the beginning of this year , for example , the Shanghai Stock Exchange and Shenzhen Stock Exchange issued detailed rules for the implementation of share buybacks by listed companies , providing detailed stock repurchase standards and guidelines for listed companies .
According to media statistics , the listed companies holding repurchase plans so far this year have been concentrated in capital construction , real estate , information technology and electronic equipment manufacturing .
In addition , in terms of repurchase payments , six listed companies have bought back more than $ 1 billion this year .
Topping the list is Yili , which has bought back more than $ 5 billion .
What impact will the repurchase of shares by a listed company have on the market ?
In an interview with reporters at the School of Finance and Finance at Renmin University of China , Vice President Zhao Xijun said that the buyback shows , on the one hand , that the listed companies have stronger economic strength and better financial position , and the ability to maintain share price stability and give investors confidence ; and on the other hand , that the listed companies and their controlling shareholders are accountable to the company , to the market and to investors .
The former is based on the company &apos;s good performance , while the latter requires the listed company and its controlling shareholders to have higher quality .
This is the most fundamental element of the capital market .
The stock repurchase of listed companies can boost investors &apos; confidence and support the stock price of listed companies .
It is also estimated that , based on the estimated number of share repurchases made by A-share listed companies since the beginning of this year and the average transaction price , the incremental capital for the A-share market is expected to exceed RMB 150 billion .
