On September 26 , Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi presided over a meeting of the Ministers for Foreign Affairs of China and the African members of the Security Council at the United Nations Headquarters in New York .
The current members of the Security Council , including the Ministers for Foreign Affairs of Côte d &apos;Ivoire , Côte d &apos;Ivoire , Equatorial Guinea , South Africa , South Africa , Niger and Tunisia , attended the meeting .
Wang Yi put forward four proposals on strengthening cooperation between China and Africa in the UN Security Council .
First , by going from strength to strength .
The biggest challenge in the current international situation is unilateralism , the direct consequence of which is the challenge of the basic norms of international relations and the erosion of the role of the United Nations , to the detriment of the interests of developing countries and small and medium-sized countries , including African countries .
Meeting this challenge requires the strength of solidarity , with China and Africa hand in hand .
In the Security Council , where three African countries speak with one voice , the weight of focus is not just three votes but the entire continent .
If China and Africa stand together , it will not be just four votes , but will drive other countries to follow suit , influencing and shaping the Council &apos;s agenda .
Since 2018 , China has established the &quot; 3 + 1 &quot; coordination mechanism with the African members of the UN Security Council .
Second , to rely on negotiations to settle disputes .
China has always advocated political settlement of hotspot issues.Africa has a good tradition of consultation and the experience of good offices of African regional and sub-regional organizations .
There are many complex challenges on the Council &apos;s agenda , particularly the African hot spots , most of which are the scourges of colonialism and some of which are directly related to external factors .
Together , we need to make good use of Chapter VI of the United Nations Charter and give full play to the role of the United Nations in the areas of good offices and mediation .
Third , they should strengthen themselves by working independently .
African countries and peoples know its problems best , and Africa has the capacity and wisdom to solve its own problems .
In dealing with African hotspot issues by the Security Council , the will of Africa should be heeded and respected , the role of regional and subregional organizations should be brought into play , and endogenous solutions from Africa should be encouraged and supported .
China is ready to strengthen coordination with Africa to firmly promote African capacity building for independent peace operations .
Fourthly , development is fundamental .
As China and the African countries are both developing countries , we must persevere in giving top priority to economic and social development and support the development path chosen by each other .
China is ready to build &quot; One Belt , One Road &quot; with the AU Agenda 2063 , the UN 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development and the development strategies of African countries , so as to help African countries enhance their capacity for development and eliminate the root causes of conflicts .
We must jointly urge the United Nations to increase investment in Africa &apos;s development .
In view of the new outbreak of the Ebola outbreak in the Democratic Republic of the Congo , China has assisted and will continue to assist with its utmost efforts , providing human and material assistance to the best of its ability.In addition , China is ready to coordinate actions with African countries and mobilize the United Nations and WHO to intensify their assistance , so as to give full play to the role of the United Nations Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
