After working around the clock for more than 1,200 days , the Da-Lai ( Li ) railway completed the construction of the No. 1 shaft of the Gaoligong mountain tunnel , which reached a depth of 762.59 meters below the surface , breaking the record of the deepest shaft of the Chinese railway tunnel .
The Gaoligong Mountains tunnel , which is 34.5 km long , is the longest tunnel in Asia , running through the Gaoligong Mountains on the west bank of the Nu River .
