Recently , Germany &apos;s Anabin database , which is responsible for the evaluation and certification of foreign qualifications , announced on its official website : Starting in 2020 , Chinese high school graduates will be able to apply for admission to a German university .
Until then , Chinese high school graduates had wanted to study at a German university for one semester ( 211,985 university ) or three semesters ( regular university ) , and had passed the APS exam or the TestAS test .
The announcement of the new rules could save at least half a year for Chinese students who want to study in Germany .
It is understood the new rules will come into force in the second half of 2019 .
Applicants must meet the requirements to complete 12 years of formal compulsory education , obtain a high school diploma , take college and university entrance examinations , and achieve a total score of 70 % or above ( or above 525 out of 750 ) , as well as a grade in two languages and one in mathematics or natural sciences .
In addition , the specific academic requirements are different .
For example , when applying for courses in the fields of medicine , stomatology , veterinary medicine , or pharmacology , the score must be at least 80 % , and the examination must include at least two courses in mathematics , physics , chemistry , biology , or sociology .
According to incomplete statistics , Chinese college entrance examination results have been recognized by many countries , including Germany , the United Kingdom , Canada and Australia .
