Tired of exercise and a tired mind ?
A study of athletes showed that after high-intensity exercise , the brain can also show signs of fatigue , the Russian Satellite Network reported .
The study , led by Mathias Pesigeron , a specialist at the Pitière-Salpetriere hospital in France , shows that there is no clear link between mental and physical labour : both require cognitive control of activity .
&quot; You need to control the autonomous process by which , when you have pain in the muscles and joints , you can force yourself to stop , &quot; he explains .
The study was carried out by the French National Institute of Physical Education and Sport ( INSEP ) .
The school expert is responsible for guiding the athletes to prepare for the Olympic Games .
Some athletes have begun to suffer from overtraining syndrome , which is a feeling of irrepressible fatigue after high-load exercise , a lack of physical recovery and a decline in performance .
INSEP poses a question : Could part of the cause of this condition be nerve fatigue , the kind of nerve fatigue caused by excessive mental work ?
The study was published in the journal Current Biology .
