Reporter 27 from the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences learned that the night moth in the Yunnan grassland has been an effective prevention and control , did not result in a large scale disaster prevention and control .
The meadow meadow greedy night moth imported from outside China was first discovered in January in Jiangcheng County in Pu &apos;er City , Yunnan . It was later confirmed in 129 counties in Yunnan , and the meadow greedy night moth gradually spread to the Chinese mainland from Yunnan , posing a direct threat to China &apos;s grain production .
The grass night moth is an important agricultural pest native to tropical and subtropical America , which has been given early warning by the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization in the world . It has the characteristics of international , itinerant , explosive and destructive .
The pest harm more than 80 types of maize , sugar cane , sorghum and other crops , large food intake , can result in the loss of up to 70 % of production .
Being difficult to control , there is no registered pesticide in China .
Since the invasion of Yunnan , the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences selected researcher Chen Aidong to lead the transboundary pests in agriculture of the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences , together with the green pest prevention and control team , to go to the front line , carry out field investigations , collect samples , and carry out technical guidance and demonstration .
Chen Aidong team has initially mastered the population characteristics , natural enemy insect resources , overseas insect source characteristics , population migration trajectories , drug toxicity and field control effects , etc .
They have actively carried out research and application of green prevention and control technology.Through the implementation of new green prevention and control technologies , such as population monitoring , adult booby-traps , scientific drug use and agronomic measures , the prevention and control effect in the demonstration areas has reached more than 90 % , reduced the use of chemical pesticides , protected the natural enemy resources and the eco-environment , and provided a technological guarantee for the effective control of outbreaks and sustainable management of the night moth in Yunnan .
At present , greedy night moth in the grassland of Yunnan Province has obtained effective prevention and control , which did not result in large scale disaster prevention and control .
The next step , the Yunnan Academy of Agricultural Sciences will focus on the outbreak of the ecological mechanism , breaking through biological control and green prevention and control technology system construction .
Meanwhile , cross-border international cooperation will be actively promoted , and efforts will be made to establish joint key laboratories and joint monitoring network sites and demonstration areas abroad , so as to enhance the comprehensive monitoring and early-warning capability of the greedy night moth in the grasslands of Yunnan Province .
