Qualification is needed for the social capital to acquire the right to manage rural land
Qualification is needed for the social capital to acquire the right of rural land management
The Measures on Rural Land Management Right Transfer Management publicly solicit opinions on the supervision of the land management right acquired by the transfer of industrial and commercial enterprises and other social capital
Yesterday , the website of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs published a notice soliciting opinions from the public on the Measures on the Transfer of the Right to Land Management Management in Rural Areas ( the Revised Draft Exposure Draft ) ( hereinafter referred to as the Draft Opinions ) , which increase the supervision and guard against the risks of acquiring the right to the management of land through the transfer of social capital , including industrial and commercial enterprises .
The Draft Opinion is now eliciting comments from the public .
The Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs stated that it had revised the Measures for the Administration of the Transfer of Rural Land Contracting and Management Rights and formed the Draft Opinions in order to implement the newly revised Rural Land Contracting Law , further consolidate and improve the rural basic management system , deepen the reform of the rural land system , and implement the &quot; separation of three rights &quot; system .
A reporter from the Beijing Youth News learned that several important changes had been made to the Draft Opinion , which was published for the first time .
The newly revised Rural Land Contract Law clarifies the scope of land circulation , implements the concept of &quot; separation of rights &quot; , establishes the terms &quot; land contract management rights &quot; and &quot; land management rights &quot; respectively in a special section , and makes a clear distinction between the transfer and interchange of land contract management rights and the transfer of land management rights ( lease , subcontract , purchase of shares or by other means ) .
In the Draft Opinions , in order to implement the concept of &quot; separation of rights &quot; and as an effective response to the thrust of the revision of the Rural Land Contracting Law , and taking into account the significant differences between the transfer of land management rights and the swap and transfer of contracted land management rights , the revised draft defined the scope of land circulation , focused on the transfer of land management rights , including leasing and purchase of shares , and changed the title of the rules from the administrative measures for the transfer of contracted land management rights to rural land to the administrative measures for the transfer of rural land management rights .
The administrative measures for the transfer and swap of the contracted management right of land will be formulated separately .
&quot; Draft Views &quot; pointed out that in the &quot; separation of three rights &quot; background , the farmer shares only the land management right for a certain period of time .
In theory , farmers are only at risk of losing their operational rights for a certain period in the event of a bankruptcy liquidation , and providing for the return of contracted land to the original contractor is therefore no longer legally necessary and in conflict with the Bankruptcy Code .
Aiming at the problem of guarding against the risk of farmers &apos; losing land , the practice produces the methods of preferred shares , shares after lease , repurchase and so on .
In view of the mature theoretical discussion of preferred shares in the Company Law , it is suggested that it should be used as an advocacy regulation to safeguard against the risk of loss of land .
